<parameter name="old_string">  {
    id: 'prompt-19',
    prompt: 'Determine your watering schedule and method by testing different approaches for 1 week',
    category: 'planning',
    helpText: 'Establishing a consistent watering routine is crucial for plant health and prevents both overwatering and drought stress in container gardens. Test different watering frequencies and times of day while monitoring soil moisture levels to find what works best for your specific plants, containers, and climate conditions. Container plants typically need more frequent watering than ground gardens, and morning watering is generally preferred to reduce disease risk and water loss to evaporation.'
  }
];</parameter>
<parameter name="new_string">  {
    id: 'prompt-19',
    prompt: 'Determine your watering schedule and method by testing different approaches for 1 week',
    category: 'planning',
    helpText: 'Establishing a consistent watering routine is crucial for plant health and prevents both overwatering and drought stress in container gardens. Test different watering frequencies and times of day while monitoring soil moisture levels to find what works best for your specific plants, containers, and climate conditions. Container plants typically need more frequent watering than ground gardens, and morning watering is generally preferred to reduce disease risk and water loss to evaporation.'
  },
  {
    id: 'prompt-20',
    prompt: 'Research and purchase a soil moisture meter to accurately monitor your plants\' water needs',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'A soil moisture meter eliminates guesswork and prevents the most common urban gardening mistakes of overwatering or underwatering plants. Purchase a basic digital or analog moisture meter (usually $10-20) and learn to use it by testing soil at different depths in your containers. This tool provides accurate readings of soil moisture levels and helps you develop proper watering instincts while protecting your plants from water-related stress that can stunt growth or kill container plants.'
  }
];</parameter>
</invoke>
