<parameter name="old_string">  {
    id: 'prompt-45',
    prompt: 'Practice proper harvesting techniques by learning to identify optimal harvest timing for each of your planted crops',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Knowing when and how to harvest is crucial for maximizing flavor, nutrition, and plant productivity in your urban garden. Learn the specific harvest indicators for each crop - herbs should be picked before flowering for best flavor, leafy greens are best harvested when young and tender, and vegetables have optimal size and color markers. Practice proper cutting techniques that encourage regrowth rather than damaging plants, such as harvesting herbs by cutting stems just above leaf nodes and picking outer lettuce leaves while leaving the center to continue growing.'
  }
];</parameter>
<parameter name="new_string">  {
    id: 'prompt-45',
    prompt: 'Practice proper harvesting techniques by learning to identify optimal harvest timing for each of your planted crops',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Knowing when and how to harvest is crucial for maximizing flavor, nutrition, and plant productivity in your urban garden. Learn the specific harvest indicators for each crop - herbs should be picked before flowering for best flavor, leafy greens are best harvested when young and tender, and vegetables have optimal size and color markers. Practice proper cutting techniques that encourage regrowth rather than damaging plants, such as harvesting herbs by cutting stems just above leaf nodes and picking outer lettuce leaves while leaving the center to continue growing.'
  },
  {
    id: 'prompt-46',
    prompt: 'Schedule and implement a weekly fertilizing routine for all your container plants based on their specific nutritional needs',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Container plants need regular feeding since nutrients wash out quickly with frequent watering and limited soil volume cannot provide ongoing nutrition like ground gardens. Research each plant\'s specific requirements and create a weekly liquid fertilizer schedule - leafy greens need nitrogen-rich feeds, flowering plants benefit from phosphorus, and fruiting vegetables require balanced nutrition throughout their growing cycle. This consistent feeding routine prevents nutrient deficiencies that can stunt growth, reduce harvests, and make plants more susceptible to pests and diseases.'
  }
];</parameter>
</invoke>
